"It was narrated that Ibn Al- Hawtakiyyah said:\"Umar, May Allah be pleased with us on the day when we stopped at Al-Qaha?' Abu Dharr said: 'I was. A rabbit was brought to the Messenger Allah and the man who brought it said: I saw it bleeding (menstruating). The Prophet did not eat, then he said: \"Eat.\" A man said: \"I am fasting.\" He said: \"What fast are you observing?\" He said: \"Three days each month\" He said: \"Why don't yo"